Perfect — your values file already contains the fix mechanism. ✅

You do NOT need to edit Helm templates manually.

This section is the key:

networkAttachmentDefinition:
  networkType: "flat"
  name:
    bh0c: ""
    bh0c_1: ""
    bh0c_2: ""
    bh0c_2_1: ""
    bh0u: ""
    bh0u_1: ""
    bh0u_2: ""
    bh0u_2_1: ""

Right now empty values cause chart defaults to be used.

The chart defaults are incorrect for your environment because they generate names with _.


---

EXACT FIX

Modify this section to explicitly use hyphenated NAD names.

Replace entire section with:

networkAttachmentDefinition:
  networkType: "flat"
  name:
    bh0c: "bscf-bh0c-nad"
    bh0c_1: "bscf-bh0c-1-nad"
    bh0c_2: "bscf-bh0c-2-nad"
    bh0c_2_1: "bscf-bh0c-2-1-nad"
    bh0u: "bscf-bh0u-nad"
    bh0u_1: "bscf-bh0u-1-nad"
    bh0u_2: "bscf-bh0u-2-nad"
    bh0u_2_1: "bscf-bh0u-2-1-nad"


---

IMPORTANT

You currently DO NOT have these NADs:

bscf-bh0c-2-nad
bscf-bh0c-2-1-nad

So create them first.


---

Create Missing NADs

Create file:

vi sriov-network-extra.yaml

Paste:

apiVersion: sriovnetwork.openshift.io/v1
kind: SriovNetwork
metadata:
  name: bscf-bh0c-2-nad
  namespace: openshift-sriov-network-operator
spec:
  resourceName: pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2
  networkNamespace: cnf
  ipam: |
    {}

---
apiVersion: sriovnetwork.openshift.io/v1
kind: SriovNetwork
metadata:
  name: bscf-bh0c-2-1-nad
  namespace: openshift-sriov-network-operator
spec:
  resourceName: pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2_1
  networkNamespace: cnf
  ipam: |
    {}

Apply:

oc apply -f sriov-network-extra.yaml


---

Verify NADs

Run:

oc get net-attach-def -n cnf

You should now see:

bscf-bh0c-2-nad
bscf-bh0c-2-1-nad


